# Meatballs

> Great to make extras. #beef #ingredient #freezer #italian #emma

![](B29601BD-EA41-4E23-8DBE-48A498423ADC.jpeg)

- Beef | Ground, 1 lb | 
- Pork | Ground, 1 lb | 
- Garlic | 2 cloves | Minced
- Eggs | 2 | 
- Parmesan Cheese | 1 cup | Freshly grated
- Parsley | 1/4 cup | Chopped
- Salt | to taste | 
- Black Pepper | to taste | 

Combine beef and pork in a large bowl. Add garlic, eggs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper

- Bread Crumbs | 1 cup | 
- Water | Â½ cup | 

Blend bread crumbs into meat mixture. Add the water. The mixture should be very moist but still hold its shape if rolled into meatballs. Shape into meatballs

- Olive Oil | 1/4 cup | 

Heat olive oil in a large skillet. Dear meatballs in batches. When the meatball is brown on all sides remove from heat and place on a sheet tray.

> Use a non-stick pan to prevent excessive sticking.

Cook meatballs in oven until thermometer reads 155 degrees.
